cc:Work.dc:title: Elvie #015
cc:Work.dc:description:
[Panel 1 - Elvie is dressed as a journalist] Elvie: Today I'm interviewing Larry Wall, the creator of Perl.
[Panel 2] Elvie: So, Larry, what do you say to the criticism that Perl just looks like a cat has walked over the keyboard?
[Panel 3 - Elvie is talking to a caricature version of Larry Wall, who is speaking in code that looks similar to classic swear words in comic strips]
Larry: $_=#@*!! ("I really don't ") ;s!d.*!!;s*re*\x74ot*;sub _{print $_.@_[0]."\n";s!@*!!}_ ("agree!")
Elvie: Larry! Please mind your language!
